</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption pageId="7" pageNumber="8" startId="7.[151,164,1810,1831]" targetBox="[192,1330,207,1767]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1422,1810,1972]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
FIG. 2. Resulting MrBayes tree from Bayesian analysis of the Cyt- 
<emphasis box="[817,829,1810,1831]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">b</emphasis>
dataset under a GTR+G model of sequence evolution. The analysis was rooted using 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[401,580,1838,1859]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Doryrhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyclops">
<emphasis box="[401,580,1838,1859]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Doryrhina cyclops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(not shown). Support values for both the ML and BA analysis are shown, with posterior probabilities converted to percentages. Clades referring to the 
<taxonomicName box="[755,879,1866,1887]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="commersonii">
<emphasis box="[755,879,1866,1887]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">commersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups identified in 
<bibRefCitation author="RAKOTOARIVELO, A. R. &amp; S. WILLOWS- MUNRO &amp; M. C. SCHOEMAN &amp; J. M. LAMB &amp; S. M. GOODMAN" box="[1159,1421,1866,1887]" journalOrPublisher="BMC Evolutionary Biology" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1" part="15" refId="ref14502" refString="RAKOTOARIVELO, A. R., S. WILLOWS- MUNRO, M. C. SCHOEMAN, J. M. LAMB, and S. M. GOODMAN. 2015. Cryptic diversity in Hipposideros commersoni sensu stricto (Chiroptera: Hipposideridae) in the western portion of Madagascar. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 15: 1." title="Cryptic diversity in Hipposideros commersoni sensu stricto (Chiroptera: Hipposideridae) in the western portion of Madagascar" type="journal article" year="2015">
Rakotoarivelo 
<emphasis box="[1302,1345,1866,1887]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
are highlighted. Samples sequenced as part of this study, including a re-sequenced sample of 
<taxonomicName authority="FMNH" authorityName="FMNH" box="[1040,1214,1895,1916]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis box="[1040,1140,1895,1916]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">H. vittatus</emphasis>
FMNH
</taxonomicName>
192857 from Pemba, are highlighted in bold. See Table 1 for definitions of acronyms. Where sampling sites are known for Malagasy samples, the site is given followed by the code MG to indicate Madagascar
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption pageId="8" pageNumber="9" startId="8.[133,146,1552,1573]" targetBox="[144,1909,516,1451]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[133,1932,1552,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
FIG. 3. Time tree resulting from MCMCTREE analysis in PAML using the MrBayes topology shown in Fig. 1. The analysis was constrained using two calibrations, one applied to the root and a fossil calibration applied to the split between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[625,754,1580,1601]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinonycteridae" genus="Rhinonicteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[625,754,1580,1601]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Rhinonicteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[800,880,1580,1601]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinonycteridae" genus="Cloeotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[800,880,1580,1601]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cloeotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Materials and Methods for details). Numbers at nodes are divergence time estimates in millions of years. 95% confidence intervals for each node are denoted by grey bars. See Table 1 for definitions of acronyms
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="synonymic_list">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,764,178,338]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
